Find your more with Mohawk!
At Mohawk Industries, we’re committed to more – more customer solutions, more process improvements, more sustainable manufacturing and more opportunities for our people.

As a Fortune 500, global flooring leader with some of the best-known brands in the industry, Mohawk is a great place to start or develop your career with an emphasis on more of what’s important to you. Come find your “more” with Mohawk!


Job ID: 50471
Title: Senior Business Intelligence Specialist
Company: Mohawk Industries, Inc.
Location: 1155 Roberts Blvd., Suite 200, Kennesaw, GA 30144

JOB DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES:
Works with Global Information Systems - Center of Excellence (COE) colleagues and project sponsors/customers to determine the long-term application architecture and strategy;
Oversees major applications integration efforts, this includes but not limited to: designs, codes, tests, installs, and supports complex integrated application systems;
Guides the customization, implementation and support of purchased package applications;
Analyzes and provides technical advice and direction regarding the interface/integrate of supported systems with the rest of the application portfolio;
Analyzes how the supported applications can best serve business functions;
Recognizes the impact to the business of proposed application changes and advises IS colleagues accordingly;
Interacts with customers, Business Process Specialist and vendors to quantify system requirements, and coordinate system integration testing, migration and roll-out;
Identifies, evaluates and recommends alternative technical solutions for best fit to business;
Oversees the initial pilot and recommends guidelines and standards for use;
Serves as Project Manager or participates on project teams on strategic long-range and highly complex projects that span the organization, crossing business unit boundaries;
As a project manager, will be responsible for overseeing and coordinating the activities of assigned project team to meet project milestones;
Proactively reviews and interprets performance against operating plans and standards;
Provides information and reports to subordinates on interpretation of results and approves changes in plans;
Presents reports on project performance, changes, scope variations, and other related matters and/or participates in key management activities committees advising project sponsors or senior management accordingly; and
Performs other duties as required.
MINIMUM EDUCATION/EXPERIENCE REQUIREMENTS:
Bachelor of Science degree in Computer Engineering, Computer Science, Business Administration, Engineering, Information Technology or a related discipline with an information technology focus;
9 years of experience managing systems developing in new computing architecture and environments;
9 years of experience with BI (Business Intelligence) development and architecture design;
7 years of experience working with EACH BI (Business Intelligence) system:
SAP BOBJ
SAP HANA
Analysis for Office
Microsoft SSAS
Tableau
SAP ERP
SAP ABAP
SDA
SLT
SAP BODS
5 years of experience developing Enterprise BI (Business Intelligence) Solution on multiple EDW (Enterprise Data Warehouse) platforms (SQLServer, HANA);
7 years of experience with integration of SAP BOBJ and SAP HANA;
5 years of experience using SAP Data Services Extractors;
5 years of experience implementing EACH of the following:
SDI
SAP BOBJ
Tableau
Power BI
SAP Analytics Cloud on HANA
7 years of experience with understanding and application of data structures and data formats which include structured, unstructured, semi-structured, JSON, XML, and EDI;
7 years of extensive experience with EACH of the following:
HANA modeling using Graphical views
SQL scripted views
Stored procedures
Table functions
7 years of experience with EDW (Enterprise Data Warehouse) development life cycle from business requirement gathering to develop end to end solutions;
9 years of experience in EACH: Self-service BI and Agile BI development; and
9 years of experience with customer service skills.
Requires less than 5% domestic travel.
Experience may be gained concurrently.

Mohawk Industries is a leading global flooring manufacturer that creates products to enhance residential and commercial spaces around the world. Mohawk’s vertically integrated manufacturing and distribution processes provide competitive advantages in the production of carpet, rugs, ceramic tile, laminate, wood, stone and vinyl flooring. Our industry-leading innovation has yielded products and technologies that differentiate our brands in the marketplace and satisfy all remodeling and new construction requirements. Our brands are among the most recognized in the industry and include American Olean, Daltile, Durkan, IVC, Karastan, Marazzi, Mohawk, Mohawk Home, Pergo, and Quick-Step. During the past decade, Mohawk has transformed its business from an American carpet manufacturer into the world’s largest flooring company with operations in Australia, Brazil, Canada, Europe, India, Malaysia, Mexico, New Zealand, Russia and the United States.

Mohawk Industries, Inc. is an Equal Opportunity Employer including disability/veteran committed to an inclusive workplace and a proud Drugs Don’t Work participant.
